            <h2>What is HTML5?</h2>
            <p>HTML5 is the standard markup language used to create web pages. It introduces semantic elements that improve accessibility and structure.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="requirements">
            <h2>Requirements for Creating an HTML5 Webpage</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Apply proper document structure with metadata in the <code>&lt;head&gt;</code>.</li>
                <li>Use semantic sectioning elements for meaningful organization.</li>
                <li>Enhance readability with text-level semantics.</li>
                <li>Include hyperlinks with meaningful attributes.</li>
                <li>Validate your HTML using the <a href="https://validator.w3.org/" target="_blank">W3C Markup Validator</a>.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>

        <section id="table-example">
